cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE 

This paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning techniques for information extraction in the biomedical domain. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the use of distributional semantics and semi-supervised learning, which are relevant to sub-categories such as cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper mentions the use of neural networks, which is relevant to sub-category cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
